---
source: crates/vize/src/cli.rs
expression: "command_help(\"fmt\")"
---
Format Vue, JSX, and TSX files

Usage: fmt [OPTIONS] [PATTERNS]...

Arguments:
  [PATTERNS]...
          Glob pattern(s) to match .vue, .jsx, and .tsx files

          [default: ./**/*.vue ./**/*.jsx ./**/*.tsx]

Options:
      --check
          Check formatting without writing (exit with error if files need formatting)

  -w, --write
          Write formatted output to files

  -c, --config <CONFIG>
          Config file path

      --no-config
          Do not load a config file

      --single-quote[=<SINGLE_QUOTE>]
          Use single quotes instead of double quotes

          [possible values: true, false]

      --print-width <PRINT_WIDTH>
          Print width (line length) for formatting

      --tab-width <TAB_WIDTH>
          Number of spaces per indentation level

      --use-tabs[=<USE_TABS>]
          Use tabs instead of spaces for indentation

          [possible values: true, false]

      --no-semi
          Do not print semicolons at the ends of statements

      --sort-attributes[=<SORT_ATTRIBUTES>]
          Sort HTML attributes in template

          [possible values: true, false]

      --single-attribute-per-line[=<SINGLE_ATTRIBUTE_PER_LINE>]
          Put each HTML attribute on its own line

          [possible values: true, false]

      --max-attributes-per-line <MAX_ATTRIBUTES_PER_LINE>
          Maximum number of attributes per line before wrapping

      --normalize-directive-shorthands[=<NORMALIZE_DIRECTIVE_SHORTHANDS>]
          Normalize directive shorthands (v-bind: → :, v-on: → @, v-slot: → #)

          [possible values: true, false]

      --profile
          Show detailed timing profile

      --slow-threshold <SLOW_THRESHOLD>
          Slow file threshold in milliseconds for profile output

          [default: 100]

  -h, --help
          Print help
